data.title: Bhojpuri singer Kalpana Patowary joins regional party Asom Gana Parishad

data.text:
Synopsis

Patowary who is known for Bhojpuri songs formally joined the regional party in Guwahati. Patowary was earlier associated with BJP. AGP is an ally in ruling BJP led government. She declared, “She joined AGP for she wanted to work for Assam.”

Guwahati: Popular folk singer Kalpana Patowary on Friday joined regional party Asom Gana Parishad (AGP).

Patowary who is known for Bhojpuri songs formally joined the regional party in Guwahati. Patowary was earlier associated with BJP.

AGP is an ally in ruling BJP led government. She declared, “She joined AGP for she wanted to work for Assam.”

Meanwhile around 700 workers, leaders of the United Bodo People's Organisation (UBPO) joined BJP.

Chief minister, Sarbananda Sonowal tweeted, “I welcome all members of the United Bodo People's Organisation to the @BJP4Assam family. Glad to be part of this historic joining ceremony of over 700 members of the Bodo community from outside BTR, led by UBPO president Shri Mihiniswar Basumatary. @RanjeetkrDass @himantabiswa.”

He added, “With the new induction, @BJP4Assam has now upto 52 lakh karyakartas, a proof of our ever growing strength. I am certain the new inductees will contribute their best in nation building, realising PM Shri @narendramodi ji's ideal of 'Sabka Saath, Sabka Vikas, Sabka Vishwas'.”
